1
00:00:00,700 --> 00:00:03,240
Everyone tells you to learn from native speakers.

2
00:00:04,050 --> 00:00:05,290
We think that's wrong.

3
00:00:05,850 --> 00:00:08,880
Learn from the native speaker who already thinks like you.

4
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,300
You don't think in English. You already know how you think.

5
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,900
The hard part is expressing those same thoughts in another language.

6
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
We don't analyze your vocabulary.

7
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,960
We analyze how you build ideas.

8
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,170
Then we verify every claim.

9
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,320
Only then

10
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,730
we look for the best role model.

11
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,240
They don't use the same words.

12
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,630
They use the same way of thinking.

13
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,400
GPT-5.6 doesn't analyze your English.

14
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:46,780
It reasons about how you organize ideas.

15
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:03,510
Codex helped us build and iterate on the system.

16
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:20,100
Instead of searching through millions of videos, you discover the one person

17
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:24,200
who already explains the world the way your mind understands it.

18
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,400
And it runs both ways. Even a small creator can come here —

19
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:34,420
to be discovered by the exact people who already think the way they explain the world.

20
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,970
Today, we help you find someone who already thinks like you.

21
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:52,790
Tomorrow, we might understand how you learn well enough to help you become someone else's role model.
